@page "/documentation/week3"

<PageTitle>Week 3 Documentation</PageTitle>

<div class="container mt-4 mb-5 pb-5">
    <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mb-4">
        <h1 class="fw-bold text-danger"><i class="bi bi-eye-slash me-2"></i> Week 3 Training: Hide & Show Input Sections</h1>
    </div>
    
    <p class="lead text-muted mb-5">This guide demonstrates how to toggle visibility of Search and Create forms dynamically using both C# Server-Side states and Client-Side Javascript.</p>

    <!-- STEP 1: UI STRUCTURE -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm border-0 mb-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-dark text-white fw-bold fs-5">
            Step 1: HTML Section Setup
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="fw-bold text-secondary">A. Defining Content Sections</h5>
            <p>Group your components logically into Search, List, and Create sections with identifying IDs.</p>
            <pre class="bg-dark text-light p-3 border rounded"><code>
&lt;!-- 2. Record searching input section --&gt;
&lt;div id="searchSection" class="card"&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;Search Records&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;button @@onclick="ToggleCreateMode"&gt;Go To Create Form&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- 3. Search result listing section --&gt;
&lt;div id="listSection" class="table-responsive"&gt;
    &lt;table&gt;...&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- 1. Record creation input section --&gt;
&lt;div id="createSection" class="card"&gt;
    &lt;h1&gt;Create New Target&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;button @@onclick="ToggleSearchMode"&gt;Back to Search&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
            </code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- STEP 2: SERVER-SIDE HIDDEN BLOCKS (BLAZOR C#) -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm border-0 mb-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white fw-bold fs-5">
            Step 2: Server-Side Logic (Blazor / C#)
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="fw-bold text-secondary">A. Using Boolean Flags (Server-Side Javascript/C#)</h5>
            <p>Blazor naturally handles state on the server. We use an <code>@@if()</code> block to show or hide the sections cleanly. When the boolean updates, the designated section hides or mounts instantly.</p>
            <pre class="bg-dark text-light p-3 border rounded"><code>
&lt;!-- 4. Hide & Show section using server side logic --&gt;

@@if (isCreatingRecord) 
{
    &lt;div id="createSection"&gt;
        &lt;h3&gt;New Record Form&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;button @@onclick="() =&gt; isCreatingRecord = false"&gt;Back to Search&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
}
else 
{
    &lt;div id="searchSection"&gt;
        &lt;h3&gt;Search & List&lt;/h3&gt;
        &lt;button @@onclick="() =&gt; isCreatingRecord = true"&gt;+ Add New Record&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
}

@@code {
    // 1 & 2. Toggling visibility between sections
    private bool isCreatingRecord = false;
}
            </code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- STEP 3: CLIENT-SIDE HIDDEN BLOCKS (JSInterop) -->
    <div class="card shadow-sm border-0 mb-4">
        <div class="card-header bg-warning text-dark fw-bold fs-5">
            Step 3: Client-Side Logic (Javascript)
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="fw-bold text-secondary">A. Pure Javascript DOM Manipulation</h5>
            <p>Sometimes you need pure UI shifts without server round-trips. We can achieve this via JS Interop calling direct <code>style.display</code> commands in the user's browser context.</p>
            
            <p><strong>Step A: Implement JS in <code>wwwroot/app.js</code></strong></p>
            <pre class="bg-dark text-light p-3 border rounded"><code>
window.uiInterop = {
    // 3. Hide & show section using client side javascript.
    showCreateForm: function() {
        document.getElementById("searchSection").style.display = 'none';
        document.getElementById("listSection").style.display = 'none';
        document.getElementById("createSection").style.display = 'block';
    },
    showSearchForm: function() {
        document.getElementById("searchSection").style.display = 'block';
        document.getElementById("listSection").style.display = 'block';
        document.getElementById("createSection").style.display = 'none';
    }
};
            </code></pre>

            <p><strong>Step B: Call from Blazor Razor code</strong></p>
            <pre class="bg-dark text-light p-3 border rounded"><code>
@@inject IJSRuntime JS

&lt;button @@onclick='() =&gt; JS.InvokeVoidAsync("uiInterop.showCreateForm")'&gt;
    Show Create (JS)
&lt;/button&gt;

&lt;div id="searchSection"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="listSection"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="createSection" style="display: none;"&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
            </code></pre>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
